div.p:
A.S. Truly M.S. is very ſubtile, who of a Negative infers an Affirmative; even as if I ſhould conclude thus: M. S. is not divers Schiſmaticks or Hereticks; Ergo, He is one Heretick: This man hath not committed divers Adulteries;


                  Ergo, He hath committed one Adultery. Have you never learned, good M.S. that old Rhime, wherein there is more Reaſon then Poetrie:


Syllogiſari, non eſt ex Particulari;

Neve Negativis, rectè concludere ſi vis:
